          "type": "assistant",
          "text": "Here’s what’s going on:\n\n## There isn’t a setting for this\n\nCodeScene’s settings don’t control how many review findings appear on one Code Vision line. The Problems view and Code Vision use different mechanisms, so they won’t always match.\n\n## Why you only see one review smell on the line\n\nThe JetBrains **Code Vision** API effectively allows **only one entry per provider for a given anchor/range**. Your team documented that in `DECISIONLOG.md`: multiple lenses from the **same** provider at the **same** place get collapsed (often only the **last** one wins).\n\nReview findings are emitted by a **single** provider, `AggregatedSmellCodeVisionProvider`, which loops all smell categories and adds a lens per smell. When several smells share the same highlight range (e.g. all on the method at line 13), they still share that **one provider id**, so the platform ends up showing **one** of them—often the last in the internal order (which fits seeing **Deep, Nested Complexity** and not Bumpy Road / Duplication).\n\nSo this is **not** something you can turn off in the IDE; it follows from how Code Vision works plus how the plugin registers lenses.\n\n## “CodeScene ACE” on the same line\n\n**CodeScene ACE** is a **different** Code Vision provider (`AceCodeVisionProvider`). It can show next to the review lens because it’s a separate provider, but it only reflects **ACE / refactor** context (e.g. opening ACE), **not** the full list of review code smells.\n\n## What would need to change to show “all” on the bar\n\nThat requires a **plugin change**, for example:\n\n1. **One combined lens** per range: e.g. text like `Bumpy Road · Code Duplication · Deep, Nested Complexity` (and sensible click behavior for multiple docs), or  \n2. **Separate `codeVisionProvider` extensions per smell category** again, as described in the decision log, so each category is a different provider and the platform can show multiple lines.\n\nIf you want this behavior in the product, the next step is a change in this repo (or a feature request to the CodeScene team) rather than an IDE toggle.\n\n[REDACTED]"
